$interpreted: Misa: Snake God, Snake Goddess, we entreat you to guide us——
Orphan: Joshua!? What are you doing hiding here?
Joshua: Shhhh!
Joshua: Hey, don't go in there! Come back!
Orphan: It's Misa! I knew it!
Joshua: Hey, be quiet!
Misa: ...You're disturbing my prayers. What do you want?
Joshua: Nothing! Nothing!
Joshua: Hey, you all get outta here!
Orphan: Joshua's obviously just trying to get a look at Misa! Joshua and Misa, sitting in a tree! K-I-S-S-I-N-G!
Joshua: Sh-Sh-Shut up!
Orphan: Haha, come on. You know you like it.
Joshua: You shut your mouth, I do not——
Misa: ...Nonsense!
Orphan: Geez, so angry...
Joshua: Misa...
Misa: If you don't become more pious, the Snake God will surely punish you! Just like Louie and Wendy!
Joshua: ——Misa!
Orphan: Hey, Louie and Wendy got so sick that they almost died. Why would you say such a thing!?
Orphan: How can you be so mean!?
Misa: I've said nothing wrong! Who told them to be so naughty whenever the High Priest came!?
Joshua: Okay, okay! Both of you, that's enough!
Orphan: Yeah, yeah, yeah. Misa's such a good girl, we're all just bad children. If we die, that must mean we deserve it!
Misa: That's not what I said——
Orphan: We're going to go play. All the good children will stay here and pray all by themselves! Come on, Joshua!
Joshua: Wait...
Misa: The flower of a Hermish Pagooda and...
Misa: ...found it. A Bunny Bloom!
Misa: Yes. Now just have to find the leaf of a Serket Stalk..........and today's job is done...
Joshua: Ah!
Joshua: ...Oh, h-h-hi, Misa...how you doing...
Misa: Not good. Why are you always following me?
Joshua: ...Leaving the orphanage to look for food is a group activity. I was afraid if you went into the wilderness alone, it'd be dangerous...
Misa: Thank you, but I'm fine. The Snake God will look after me.
Joshua: Wait, listen to me! I'll go with you to apologize to everyone. After everyone calms down, they won't exclude you from everything. How about it?
Misa: ...No.
Joshua: Misa, don't be such a crabby pa——
Misa: I won't apologize. I didn't do anything wrong! If nobody wants to pay attention to me then I don't care!  I'm not acting crabby!
Joshua: You can't talk like that. Louie and Wendy got a strange sickness and aren't getting better. Everybody is worried, and then you said that...
Misa: I'm worried about them too. That's why I was praying for them! And you all interrupted me!
Misa: If the Snake God gets even angrier and makes it worse, what then!?
Joshua: Oh, that's why you were angry...
Joshua: ...I'm sorry. We misunderstood you. Let's go back and explain it to everyone——
Joshua: Be careful!
Misa: Joshua!
Misa: Joshua! Get up, Joshua! Snake God and Goddess, I beg you——
Joshua: ...Mi...sa?
Misa: Did...the blood stop?
Joshua: ...It...doesn't really hurt anymore...
Misa: What...what's happening to me?
Joshua: We'll figure it out later. That thing is coming back!
Devious: By the mercy of the Snake God and Goddess. This is a miracle...
Devious: Hssss, amazing...this ability is truly amazing...
Devious: I know you. You're the child from the orphanage, no? I was just planning on going to see all of you.
Devious: What's your name?
